===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|comete|lang=fro}} (French: ''[[comète]]''), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|cometes|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|κομήτης||longhaired|sc=polytonic|tr=komētēs|lang=grc}}, referring to the tail of a comet, from {{term|κόμη||hair|sc=polytonic|tr=komē|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|astronomy|lang=en}} A [[celestial body]] consisting mainly of [[ice]], [[dust]] and [[gas]] in a (usually very [[eccentric]]) [[orbit]] around the [[Sun]] and having a "tail" of matter blown back from it by the [[solar wind]] as it approaches the Sun.
# A celestial phenomenon with the appearance given by the orbiting celestial body.
# Any of several species of [[hummingbird]] found in the [[Andes]].

